    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling performance today, anchored by the elite profile of **Kyle Tucker**. With an efficiency score of 81.60, **Kyle Tucker** is our undisputed anchor, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Paddack and advantageous wind conditions that boost his base projection. Joining him in the must-start tier are **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.71) and **Andy Pages** (65.13). **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** continues to showcase high-end contact metrics against Suarez, while **Andy Pages** receives a double-digit bump from Paddack\u2019s high xERA and strong wind conditions in his favor. While **Miguel Vargas** (59.40) and **Nolan Schanuel** (54.98) represent solid, middle-tier production, we are tracking 40% rain risks for both; if the game is delayed, we lose precious plate appearances that could hurt our daily point totals.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (54.77). Despite his power potential, **Marcell Ozuna** was edged out by **Nolan Schanuel** and **Miguel Vargas** due to unfavorable wind conditions\u2014specifically a \"Wind In\" factor\u2014which penalized his total efficiency score. Similarly, **Josh Jung** (47.87) fell short of the threshold, as his matchup against Fried presents too much friction to justify a start over our currently active lineup. Meanwhile, we continue to monitor the situation for **Liam Hicks** (42.45), who faces the toughest assignment of the day against Yamamoto; he remains in the lineup to preserve our game caps, but he carries the lowest expected margin for error. We will be watching the weather closely in those 1B/3B spots to see if any late-scratch risks force us to deploy reinforcements from the bench.",
